# Button Component Example (React)

This is a simple React example that demonstrates how to use a reusable **Button component** and pass a function to it as a prop.

---

## ðŸ“Œ What this code does

When the **Submit** button is clicked, it logs `"Submitted"` to the browser console.

---

## ðŸ§© Example Usage

```jsx
<div className="card">
  <Button
    text="Submit"
    onClickHandler={() => console.log('Submitted')}
  />
</div>
